description: Orange County investigates double shooting of teens

story_text:
Teenagers hospitalized after late-night shooting in Orange County Teenagers hospitalized after late-night shooting in Orange County. Orange County investigates double shooting of teens . . Updated: 4:11 AM EDT Jun 11, 2021
				. . . . . . Two teenagers were shot Thursday night in Orange County, according to authorities.  The teens, an 18 year-old young man and a 16 year-old boy received gunshot wounds, have been transported to an area hospital.  The incident happened shortly before 10 p.m. Thursday near a gas station along Forest City Road, just north of Kennedy Boulevard.Authorities have not released a suspect description, and have not provided the condition of the teenagers.WESH 2 News Sunrise will continue to follow this breaking news story as the Orange County Sheriff's Office updates information. ORANGE COUNTY, Fla. — Two teenagers were shot Thursday night in Orange County, according to authorities.  The teens, an 18 year-old young man and a 16 year-old boy received gunshot wounds, have been transported to an area hospital. The incident happened shortly before 10 p.m. Thursday near a gas station along Forest City Road, just north of Kennedy Boulevard. Authorities have not released a suspect description, and have not provided the condition of the teenagers. WESH 2 News Sunrise will continue to follow this breaking news story as the Orange County Sheriff's Office updates information. . . .
title: Teenagers hospitalized after late-night shooting in Orange County
